For {= parent_clade =}+ Y-DNA haplogroup parent clades — paternal lineages on the human Y-chromosome phylogenetic tree, identified by SNP-derived labels (e.g., R-M269) — report at least {= child_clade =} direct child clades (one phylogenetic step removed) along with each child's TMRCA estimate (either the formation date when the SNP arose, or the MRCA date for the child clade's extant members) and supply a page (i.e. at least {= url =} URLs per parent-child pair) from a recognized Y-DNA-phylogeny source.

Requirements:
- The page must communicate (possibly via URL) that it is the per-(child clade) primary-source record.
- The page must name the child clade by its SNP-derived label as the page's primary subject, accepting canonical-equivalent forms across SNP-naming variants.
- The page must identify the parent clade as the *immediate* ancestor of the child clade — one phylogenetic step up, not any older ancestor.
- The page ought to report a TMRCA estimate for the child clade matching the claim within {= tmrca_tolerance =} of the page's reported value.
